The paper deals with coding problems related to information theory and signal processing, which are typically covered in the arXiv categories of cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability), and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of Slepian-Wolf and Wyner-Ziv codes, which are commonly used in source coding and compression, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to the arXiv categories of cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
